The Pongola Regional Court has convicted and sentenced five suspects to a collective four life terms and a total of 225 years imprisonment for crimes committed on local farms from December 2014 to March 2015.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
The group of armed men, said police in a statement, would rob farms within the Pongola and Magudu policing precincts and rob farmers of their valuables, including firearms and proceed to rape the women. Numerous cases were opened at Pongola and Magudu police stations.
"A task team was tasked with investigating these cases, which subsequently led to the arrest and prosecution of the accused."
The investigating team received intelligence about a group who were planning on attacking another farm. The task team went to the farm where they found the accused hiding in the bushes.
READ: #CrimeStats: Outrage as farm attacks and murders ignored
Some of the criminals were able to flee the scene, while two of them, including a female were apprehended, and found to have rifles in their possession.
Wandile Gabriel Dlamini, 25, was sentenced to life imprisonment for rape,with 70 years for robbery with aggravating circumstances,  
Mlungisi Thabathu Mathenjwa, 21, and Phumlani Sotsha Mdluli, 28, were each sentenced to life imprisonment for rape, with 45 years for robbery with aggravating circumstances.
Ntokozo Prince Mthethwa, 23, sentenced to life imprisonment for rape, 30 years for robbery with aggravating circumstances and 15 years for possession of firearm and ammunition and, the fifth accused, Khethiwe Gugu Gumbi, 34, was sentenced to 20 years imprisonment for illegal possession of a rifle.
